{
  "children":[
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The course of an individual's life events and experiences."}],"type":"paragraph"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Word Breakdown"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"人生 combines the concepts of humanity and existence into life experience."}],"type":"paragraph"},
    {"align":[],"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Component"}],"type":"tableCell"},{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Meaning"}],"type":"tableCell"}],"type":"tableRow"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"人"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"tableCell"},{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Person, human being - pictograph of a standing figure"}],"type":"tableCell"}],"type":"tableRow"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"生"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"tableCell"},{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Life, birth, living - plant (屮) growing from earth (一)"}],"type":"tableCell"}],"type":"tableRow"}],"type":"table"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The combination suggests the uniquely human experience of conscious, meaningful existence."}],"type":"paragraph"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Core Meaning & Usage"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"人生 represents "},{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"the totality of human experience and existence"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":". It's used:"}],"type":"paragraph"},
    {"children":[{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Life philosophy"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":": 人生观 (rénshēngguān) - \"outlook on life\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Life stages"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":": 人生阶段 (rénshēng jiēduàn) - \"stages of life\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Life meaning"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":": 人生意义 (rénshēng yìyì) - \"meaning of life\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Life experiences"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":": 人生经历 (rénshēng jīnglì) - \"life experiences\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"}],"ordered":true,"spread":false,"start":1,"type":"list"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Examples"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"人生如梦"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (rénshēng rú mèng) - \"life is like a dream\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"人生道路"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (rénshēng dàolù) - \"path of life\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"人生目标"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (rénshēng mùbiāo) - \"life goals\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"人生感悟"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (rénshēng gǎnwù) - \"life insights\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"美好人生"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (měihǎo rénshēng) - \"beautiful life\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"}],"ordered":false,"spread":false,"start":null,"type":"list"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cultural Context"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"人生 carries profound philosophical weight in Chinese culture, reflecting millennia of contemplation\nabout human existence. It encompasses Confucian ideals of moral cultivation, Daoist concepts of\nharmony with nature, and Buddhist notions of impermanence. The phrase \"人生如戏\" (rénshēng rú xì) -\n\"life is like a play\" - reflects the theatrical metaphor often used to discuss life's roles and\nperformances. In Chinese thought, 人生 is not just biological existence but the opportunity for\nmoral and spiritual development, making it central to discussions of purpose, meaning, and personal\nfulfillment."}],"type":"paragraph"}
